    "body": "<p> </p>\n<p>You work for the Delhi Traffic Police and the odd even scheme is in place. A stream of cars are approaching the traffic checkpoint. Today is an even day. You can collect fines only from cars with odd numbers on their number plates. You may stop 2 consecutive cars at a time ( except the last car which can be stopped alone ), and fine the defaulters. But when you do stop 2 cars, the next car in line flees only if it's a defaulter. You may also choose to let off cars one at a time. What is the maximum number of cars that you can fine?</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line of the input contains an integer <b>T</b> denoting the number of test cases. The description of <b>T</b> test cases follows.\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer <b>N</b> denoting the number of cars.\n The second line contains <b>N</b> space-separated positive integers <b>A<sub>1</sub></b>, <b>A<sub>2</sub></b>, ... <b>A<sub>N</sub></b> denoting the number plate of the i-th car. The cars approach from left to right, i.e <b>A<sub>1</sub></b> is the first car to approach the checkpoint, followed by <b>A<sub>2</sub></b> and so on.\n</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case, output a single line containing a single integer denoting the maximum cars you can fine.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>10</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>A<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>100000000</b> </li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n3\n3\n1 3 5\n7\n1 2 3 5 6 7 9\n6\n1 2 3 4 5 7\n<b>Output:</b>\n2\n4\n3\n</pre>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b> Stop <b>A<sub>1</sub></b> and <b>A<sub>2</sub></b>. Collect fines from both cars. <b>A<sub>3</sub></b> flees.</p>\n<p><b>Example case 2.</b> Let off <b>A<sub>1</sub></b> and <b>A<sub>2</sub></b>. Stop <b>A<sub>3</sub></b> and <b>A<sub>4</sub></b>. Collect fines from both cars. Let off <b>A<sub>5</sub></b>. Stop <b>A<sub>6</sub></b> and <b>A<sub>7</sub></b>. Collect fines from both cars.</p>\n<p><b>Example case 3.</b> Stop <b>A<sub>1</sub></b> and <b>A<sub>2</sub></b>. Collect fine from <b>A<sub>1</sub></b>. <b>A<sub>3</sub></b> flees. Let off <b>A<sub>4</sub></b>. Stop <b>A<sub>5</sub></b> and <b>A<sub>6</sub></b>. Collect fines from both cars.</p>\n\n",
